CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 18, 1941, pg. 3, reads: "A. F. L. Elects Officers - Newly elected officers of the American Federation of Labor.  Left to right: William E. Miller, president; Stedman Buckley, vice-president; Theodore Johnson, secretary-treasurer; Ollie Miller, three-year trustee; Zebedee Tucker, one-year trustee; Haston Bolen Jr., recording secretary.  Other members not present are West Turner."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of American Federation of Labor officers, seated from left: Theodore Johnson, Stedman Buckley; standing: William E. Miller, Ollie Miller, Haston Bolen Jr., and Zebedee Tucker gathered in interior with sign inscribed "Attention, all members of Local Union 609 are requested to attend at least one meeting each month.  Any member missing two meetings 'in succession' will be fined $1.00 ordered by Local Union 609, 2297 Centre Ave."
